# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: AloneInTheCamp
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah had kept her word and remained in the tent, but by now, it had been 2 days."
    new "Sarah had kept her word and remained in the tent, but by now, it had been 2 days."

    old "Her mind had begun to race...had something happened to Kate?"
    new "Her mind had begun to race...had something happened to Kate?"

    old "Did something go wrong with Vaelen?"
    new "Did something go wrong with Vaelen?"

    old "Sarah's mind kept going back and forth, calming herself, only to then imagine some new horror."
    new "Sarah's mind kept going back and forth, calming herself, only to then imagine some new horror."

    old "In the end, she did the only thing she had been told...she waited."
    new "In the end, she did the only thing she had been told...she waited."

    old "It was on this second day, that suddenly, the flap to the tent was pulled back."
    new "It was on this second day, that suddenly, the flap to the tent was pulled back."

    old "Two men came into the tent. Neither seemed to notice Sarah and each fell into their own bunk."
    new "Two men came into the tent. Neither seemed to notice Sarah and each fell into their own bunk."

    old "They were soldiers, that much was obvious, but they also seemed...young. No older than Sarah, she estimated."
    new "They were soldiers, that much was obvious, but they also seemed...young. No older than Sarah, she estimated."

    old "Unsure of what was happening, or what to say, Sarah kept quiet."
    new "Unsure of what was happening, or what to say, Sarah kept quiet."

    old "Not even a hello, Kate? You too good for us now?"
    new "Not even a hello, Kate? You too good for us now?"

    old "The young man turned his head towards Sarah, and suddenly shot upright."
    new "The young man turned his head towards Sarah, and suddenly shot upright."

    old "Wait, holy shit, you're not Kate! Who the hell are you?"
    new "Wait, holy shit, you're not Kate! Who the hell are you?"

    old "The other young man suddenly looked up."
    new "The other young man suddenly looked up."

    old "Huh, I thought it was Kate too..."
    new "Huh, I thought it was Kate too..."

    old "Sarah didn't know what to say, and only stared at the both of them."
    new "Sarah didn't know what to say, and only stared at the both of them."

    old "Hey, I asked you a question!"
    new "Hey, I asked you a question!"

    old "The other man motioned his friend to calm down."
    new "The other man motioned his friend to calm down."

    old "Relax, Caleb, look at her. She's scared out of her mind. Don't yell at her like that."
    new "Relax, Caleb, look at her. She's scared out of her mind. Don't yell at her like that."

    old "He reached out a hand. Sarah instinctively reached out and shook it."
    new "He reached out a hand. Sarah instinctively reached out and shook it."

    old "Ephraim."
    new "Ephraim."

    old "The man introduced himself."
    new "The man introduced himself."

    old "And that charmer over there is my friend, Caleb."
    new "And that charmer over there is my friend, Caleb."

    old "Caleb only gave a short wave as a means of introduction."
    new "Caleb only gave a short wave as a means of introduction."

    old "Now...I understand this is confusing for you...it's confusing for us...but...who are you, exactly?"
    new "Now...I understand this is confusing for you...it's confusing for us...but...who are you, exactly?"

    old "I mean, I feel like we have a right to ask first...since...this is our tent."
    new "I mean, I feel like we have a right to ask first...since...this is our tent."

    old "Sarah begin to tell her story. She noticed that once she started speaking, she couldn't stop herself."
    new "Sarah begin to tell her story. She noticed that once she started speaking, she couldn't stop herself."

    old "It wasn't wise, but she told them everything. Sharing with them made her feel better, forget about the anxiety she had felt before."
    new "It wasn't wise, but she told them everything. Sharing with them made her feel better, forget about the anxiety she had felt before."

    old "The two young men listened intently until Sarah finished her story."
    new "The two young men listened intently until Sarah finished her story."

    old "Ooh, so you're friends with Kate."
    new "Ooh, so you're friends with Kate."

    old "But I haven't seen her in...like two days. I don't know what's going on anymore. I've just been waiting here till she gets back."
    new "But I haven't seen her in...like two days. I don't know what's going on anymore. I've just been waiting here till she gets back."

    old "Ephraim shrugged, and tried to comfort Sarah."
    new "Ephraim shrugged, and tried to comfort Sarah."

    old "She does that sometimes, you know, dissapears. But she always finds her way back, don't worry."
    new "She does that sometimes, you know, dissapears. But she always finds her way back, don't worry."

    old "Caleb chimed in."
    new "Caleb chimed in."

    old "Yeah, remember when she just dissapeared for...what was it, seven days? Even I started to worry then, but there she was one day, just back, pretending it never happened."
    new "Yeah, remember when she just dissapeared for...what was it, seven days? Even I started to worry then, but there she was one day, just back, pretending it never happened."

    old "Ephraim nodded."
    new "Ephraim nodded."

    old "Did she say anything to you before she left."
    new "Did she say anything to you before she left."

    old "She just took my bag and said she was going to sort some things out. I thought it would be an hour, not...this."
    new "She just took my bag and said she was going to sort some things out. I thought it would be an hour, not...this."

    old "Caleb suddenly leaned in forward."
    new "Caleb suddenly leaned in forward."

    old "Your bag?"
    new "Your bag?"

    old "Sarah nodded. She didn't know why that was important."
    new "Sarah nodded. She didn't know why that was important."

    old "Tell me, was there anything valuable in that bag?"
    new "Tell me, was there anything valuable in that bag?"

    old "Yes, stuff for on the road, some clothes...jewelry."
    new "Yes, stuff for on the road, some clothes...jewelry."

    old "Ephraim sighed."
    new "Ephraim sighed."

    old "Yeah...you shouldn't have done that..."
    new "Yeah...you shouldn't have done that..."

    old "Sarah turned to Ephraim."
    new "Sarah turned to Ephraim."

    old "Kate isn't...very good with money. I mean, she's a decent person and all, but, don't give her anything you're not willing to lose."
    new "Kate isn't...very good with money. I mean, she's a decent person and all, but, don't give her anything you're not willing to lose."

    old "Sarah was struck by the words."
    new "Sarah was struck by the words."

    old "The idea that Kate might have stolen her belongings had never occurred to her...until now."
    new "The idea that Kate might have stolen her belongings had never occurred to her...until now."

    old "No...she's my friend...she wouldn't..."
    new "No...she's my friend...she wouldn't..."

    old "Sarah was stammering."
    new "Sarah was stammering."

    old "She grasped her own head, trying to calm her mind. She felt like her head was about to explode."
    new "She grasped her own head, trying to calm her mind. She felt like her head was about to explode."

    old "She was on the other side of the ocean...with no money...nothing at all..."
    new "She was on the other side of the ocean...with no money...nothing at all..."

    old "All on the trust she had placed in a friend she hadn't seen in years. You idiot, Sarah cursed herself."
    new "All on the trust she had placed in a friend she hadn't seen in years. You idiot, Sarah cursed herself."

    old "How could I have been this stupid..."
    new "How could I have been this stupid..."

    old "She felt Ephraim reaching out and patting her on the shoulder."
    new "She felt Ephraim reaching out and patting her on the shoulder."

    old "Hey, it will be ok. We'll just wait for Kate to come back, and we can sort it all out."
    new "Hey, it will be ok. We'll just wait for Kate to come back, and we can sort it all out."

    old "Despite everything, Sarah found herself comforted by Ephraim and Caleb."
    new "Despite everything, Sarah found herself comforted by Ephraim and Caleb."

    old "She spend the next hours with them, talking, learning more about the mercenary company and Lethram."
    new "She spend the next hours with them, talking, learning more about the mercenary company and Lethram."

    old "Sarah was happy for the company. Happy she could finally talk to someone."
    new "Sarah was happy for the company. Happy she could finally talk to someone."

    old "She learned that Ephraim and Caleb had been mercenaries for some years now."
    new "She learned that Ephraim and Caleb had been mercenaries for some years now."

    old "They grew up in the same town, and after it was burned down in a raid, decided to stick together."
    new "They grew up in the same town, and after it was burned down in a raid, decided to stick together."

    old "Ever since, they had been the closest of friends."
    new "Ever since, they had been the closest of friends."

    old "Sarah had been right, both men had been about her age, but unlike Sarah, they had been surviving in this world for years now."
    new "Sarah had been right, both men had been about her age, but unlike Sarah, they had been surviving in this world for years now."

    old "Despite this, neither seemed too burdened by their traumas. They smiled and laughed. A lot, actually. Sarah tried to remember if she ever met any two people that were this jovial."
    new "Despite this, neither seemed too burdened by their traumas. They smiled and laughed. A lot, actually. Sarah tried to remember if she ever met any two people that were this jovial."

    old "Ephraim was the more serious of the two. He was careful with his words, and his eyes hinted at a deeper intellect."
    new "Ephraim was the more serious of the two. He was careful with his words, and his eyes hinted at a deeper intellect."

    old "Caleb, on the other hand, was loud. Once he started speaking, he kept going, his hands waving around, putting force to his words."
    new "Caleb, on the other hand, was loud. Once he started speaking, he kept going, his hands waving around, putting force to his words."

    old "He had a slightly heavier build than Ephraim, but by Sarah's estimation, they seemed about as strong."
    new "He had a slightly heavier build than Ephraim, but by Sarah's estimation, they seemed about as strong."

    old "The three kept speaking for hours, until suddenly, a commotion broke out, outside of the tent, disrupting their conversation."
    new "The three kept speaking for hours, until suddenly, a commotion broke out, outside of the tent, disrupting their conversation."

    old "Ephraim took charge."
    new "Ephraim took charge."

    old "I'll see what's going on."
    new "I'll see what's going on."

    old "He threw aside the flap and walked out of the tent."
    new "He threw aside the flap and walked out of the tent."

    old "Sarah heard his voice."
    new "Sarah heard his voice."

    old "Ugh...Kate...you're a mess."
    new "Ugh...Kate...you're a mess."

    old "Upon hearing her friend's name, she crawled out the tent, followed shortly after by Caleb."
    new "Upon hearing her friend's name, she crawled out the tent, followed shortly after by Caleb."

    old "There, in the midsts of the small clearing in front of the tent, Sarah found her friend."
    new "There, in the midsts of the small clearing in front of the tent, Sarah found her friend."

    old "Kate was a mess, wobbling from side to side, her head tilting around, wildly."
    new "Kate was a mess, wobbling from side to side, her head tilting around, wildly."

    old "Sarah saw Kate was still holding a wine bottle in her right hand. Not much was left in it."
    new "Sarah saw Kate was still holding a wine bottle in her right hand. Not much was left in it."

    old "By the looks of it, Kate was several bottles deep already."
    new "By the looks of it, Kate was several bottles deep already."

    old "Sarah nearly screamed Kate's name."
    new "Sarah nearly screamed Kate's name."

    old "Kate, as if partially sobering up, suddenly looked at Sarah."
    new "Kate, as if partially sobering up, suddenly looked at Sarah."

    old "She began to sob."
    new "She began to sob."

    old "Sarah stormed up to Kate, grabbing her by the shoulders."
    new "Sarah stormed up to Kate, grabbing her by the shoulders."

    old "Where is it? Where is my stuff."
    new "Where is it? Where is my stuff."

    old "Kate only started sobbing louder. She tried hugging Sarah."
    new "Kate only started sobbing louder. She tried hugging Sarah."

    old "Sarah pushed Kate away."
    new "Sarah pushed Kate away."

    old "Tell me where you put it...please, Kate, where is my bag?"
    new "Tell me where you put it...please, Kate, where is my bag?"

    old "Upon being rejected, Kate fell to her knees. The bottle slipped from her hands and rolled away."
    new "Upon being rejected, Kate fell to her knees. The bottle slipped from her hands and rolled away."

    old "Kate's eyes were locked on the ground."
    new "Kate's eyes were locked on the ground."

    old "A small crowd had formed around the commotion."
    new "A small crowd had formed around the commotion."

    old "It's gone...all of it."
    new "It's gone...all of it."

    old "Her voice slurred."
    new "Her voice slurred."

    old "Sarah felt like she knew this, as if she had prepared for the worst when talking with Ephraim and Caleb...but hearing it, actually knowing it, felt different."
    new "Sarah felt like she knew this, as if she had prepared for the worst when talking with Ephraim and Caleb...but hearing it, actually knowing it, felt different."

    old "She felt as if she had been punched in the stomach."
    new "She felt as if she had been punched in the stomach."

    old "Kate reached out, grabbing onto Sarah's dress. She tried to look up at Sarah, her face was covered in tears."
    new "Kate reached out, grabbing onto Sarah's dress. She tried to look up at Sarah, her face was covered in tears."

    old "Sarah...I'm so sorry...please...forgive me...I'm begging you, I..."
    new "Sarah...I'm so sorry...please...forgive me...I'm begging you, I..."

    old "A loud cracking sound rang out."
    new "A loud cracking sound rang out."

    old "Kate's hands reached up, covering her cheek. Her face was stunned disbelief."
    new "Kate's hands reached up, covering her cheek. Her face was stunned disbelief."

    old "Sarah had struck her with an open hand."
    new "Sarah had struck her with an open hand."

    old "I trusted you...and you took everything from me. You dragged me here, I have nothing left...and you want me to forgive you?"
    new "I trusted you...and you took everything from me. You dragged me here, I have nothing left...and you want me to forgive you?"

    old "You're insane."
    new "You're insane."

    old "Sarah raised her hand again, but this time, she saw Kate cower. It caused her to hestitate. Then she dropped her hands past her body, sparing Kate another blow."
    new "Sarah raised her hand again, but this time, she saw Kate cower. It caused her to hestitate. Then she dropped her hands past her body, sparing Kate another blow."

    old "Was any of what you told me back at Castle Reinmeer true?"
    new "Was any of what you told me back at Castle Reinmeer true?"

    old "Kate shook her head."
    new "Kate shook her head."

    old "A moment of clarity began to dawn on Sarah, amidst all the chaos. She had thrown her life away...for this drunkard thief."
    new "A moment of clarity began to dawn on Sarah, amidst all the chaos. She had thrown her life away...for this drunkard thief."

    old "I don't want to see you, get out of my sight."
    new "I don't want to see you, get out of my sight."

    old "Sarah turned around and walked back into the tent, the only place in the world she still felt somewhat safe."
    new "Sarah turned around and walked back into the tent, the only place in the world she still felt somewhat safe."

    old "Sarah no longer turned around to look, but outside, Kate crawled up to her feet as best she could, and stumbled away, tears still streaming."
    new "Sarah no longer turned around to look, but outside, Kate crawled up to her feet as best she could, and stumbled away, tears still streaming."

